# Python-Specific Architecture

## Backend layers
- handler/view: HTTP or transport layer only, including FastAPI routes, Flask views, and Django views
- service: business logic
- repository: data access, including databases and external APIs

## Python-specific rules
- Repositories should return domain models or DTO-style objects.

## Example structure
```python
# handler (transport)
@router.post("/users")
async def create_user(request: CreateUserRequest) -> UserResponse:
    user = await user_service.create_user(request.to_domain())
    return UserResponse.from_domain(user)

# service (business logic)
class UserService:
    async def create_user(self, user_data: User) -> User:
        if await self.user_repo.exists(user_data.email):
            raise UserAlreadyExistsError()
        return await self.user_repo.save(user_data)

# repository (data access)
class UserRepository:
    async def save(self, user: User) -> User:
        ...
```
